  "prompt": "How can I control my temper?",
  "response": "Here are some strategies to help control your temper:\n\n1. Practice deep breathing\n- Take slow, deep breaths when you feel anger rising\n- This can help calm your physiological response\n\n2. Recognize triggers\n- Identify situations or people that provoke your anger\n- Develop strategies to manage or avoid these triggers\n\n3. Use relaxation techniques\n- Meditation\n- Progressive muscle relaxation\n- Yoga\n- Counting to ten\n\n4. Improve communication skills\n- Express feelings calmly and clearly\n- Use \"I\" statements\n- Listen actively\n- Avoid blaming or aggressive language\n\n5. Exercise regularly\n- Physical activity helps reduce stress and tension\n- Releases endorphins that improve mood\n\n6. Get enough sleep\n- Lack of sleep can increase irritability\n- Maintain a consistent sleep schedule\n\n7. Practice mindfulness\n- Stay present in the moment\n- Observe your emotions without reacting immediately\n\n8. Consider professional help\n- Anger management counseling\n- Therapy can help develop coping strategies\n\n9. Take a timeout\n- When feeling overwhelmed, remove yourself from the situation\n- Cool down before responding\n\n10. Use cognitive reframing\n- Challenge negative thought patterns\n- Look for alternative perspectives\n\nRemember, managing anger is a skill that improves with practice.",
